  <data name="Settings_PrivacyPolicy_Overview_Body" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>BookHeart is an offline-first book tracking app. Your data is stored locally on your device and is never transmitted to our servers. We do not collect, store, or share any personal information.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Settings_PrivacyPolicy_Storage_Title" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Data storage</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Settings_PrivacyPolicy_Storage_Body" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>All your books, reading sessions, goals, plants, and settings are stored in a local database (SQLite) on your device. This data never leaves your device unless you explicitly use the Backup &amp; Restore feature.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Settings_PrivacyPolicy_Camera_Title" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Camera permission</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Settings_PrivacyPolicy_Camera_Body" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>BookHeart requests camera access solely for scanning book barcodes (ISBN). No photos or videos are captured, stored, or transmitted. Camera access is optional and can be denied without affecting other app features.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Settings_PrivacyPolicy_Network_Title" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Network usage</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Settings_PrivacyPolicy_Network_Body" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>When you look up a book by ISBN, BookHeart sends the ISBN number to the Google Books API to retrieve book metadata (title, author, cover image). No personal data or device identifiers are included in these requests. The app functions fully offline without this feature.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Settings_PrivacyPolicy_ThirdParty_Title" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Third-party services</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Settings_PrivacyPolicy_ThirdParty_Body" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>BookHeart uses three third-party services: the Google Books API for optional ISBN lookup, Firebase Analytics for anonymous usage statistics (Android only, enabled by default, opt-out under Settings → Privacy), and Firebase Crashlytics for anonymous crash reports (Android only, enabled by default, opt-out under Settings → Privacy). Firebase never receives book titles, authors, ISBNs, quotes, annotations, or personal notes — only coarse bucketed counts. The Android Advertising ID and Android ID are explicitly disabled.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Settings_PrivacyPolicy_Deletion_Title" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Data deletion</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Settings_PrivacyPolicy_Deletion_Body" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>You can delete all your data at any time using the "Delete All Data" option in Settings. Uninstalling the app also removes all stored data from your device.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Settings_PrivacyPolicy_Children_Title" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Children's privacy</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Settings_PrivacyPolicy_Children_Body" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>BookHeart does not knowingly collect any information from children. The app does not require account creation or any personal information to function.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Settings_PrivacyPolicy_Changes_Title" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Changes to this policy</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Settings_PrivacyPolicy_Changes_Body" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Any changes to this privacy policy will be reflected in app updates. The "Last updated" date at the top indicates the most recent revision.</value>
  </data>
